Control of the city is in the hands of a "kleptocracy," leaving a portion of the bribes and protection money it collects directly to the Kremlin, the U.S. Embassy in Russia said in February.
It was reported that both the police and the Federal Security Service operate huge blackmail systems, which helps explain the high cost of living in Moscow.
They raise money not only from legitimate businesses, but also from organized criminal groups.
Each layer of the bureaucracy, what Prime Minister Vladimir Putin has termed the "vertical authority," takes its part as money climbs up the ladder.
The note, which was sent to Washington under the name Ambassador John Beyrle, was published by WikiLeaks on its website on Wednesday.
