China Maintains Greenhouse Gas Reduction Targets
The representative of that country at COP16 said that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the carbon footprint and explained that it supports its offer to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 40 and 45 percent by 2020.
China maintains its offer to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45 percent by 2020, said Su Wei, China's representative at COP16.
In his first public appearance at the 16th Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei said his country has made enormous efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and reconvert its industry.
In fact, he said, in the last four years his country has invested 245 million dollars in efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
However, he made it clear that China will not change its objectives, but will continue to work together with the international community in this matter.
He said that China's climate change strategy is divided into four areas: dialogue; capacity building; Institution building and support for pilot programs.
In all these areas, progress has been made, including the approval, last year, of a new Energy Law, which includes the objectives set in terms of reducing gas emissions, he explained.
In China, federal authorities have been working in coordination with state and local authorities to achieve the goals of energy saving, efficient energy use and emission reduction.
In addition, he added, several multi-year plans, both financed by the Chinese government and by governments of other countries, are underway or have already been concluded.
For example, he said, the Energy Efficiency Program, which was implemented during the last five years and received investments from the United Nations (UN), the government and the private initiative.
A provincial climate change project is also underway, another for the change of incandescent bulbs by savers and one more for mitigation and adaptation, he explained.
At the same table, Martin Krol, scientific adviser to the government of that country on climate change, said that China's efforts have been greater than generally thought.
For example, he said, the per capita emission of greenhouse gases in China is six tons per person, while in the United States it is 100 tons; China is responsible for 9 percent of the historical contribution to pollution.
It has also made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, such as increasing energy efficiency by 20 percent in the last five years and plans to do the same by 2020, he added.
Legality Expulsion of Espino: César Nava
The national leader of the PAN explained that the former PAN leader has the right to go to the National Order Commission to demand what suits his right.
The national leader of the PAN, César Nava Vázquez, assured that the expulsion of Manuel Espino Barrientos was in accordance with the law and that the former PAN leader has the right to go to the National Order Commission to demand what suits his right.
In an interview prior to the inauguration of Gabino Cué Monteagudo as governor of the state, he said that in any case the expulsion of Espino is a decision taken at the local level.
"This is an autonomous decision of the Order Commission of Sonora."
"Mr. Espino has his right to go, where appropriate, via complaint to the Order Commission of the National Council, so that it is a decision taken within the scope of a competent body," he noted.
On the other hand, he clarified that it is not time to think about 2012 and that an alliance for the presidential candidacy was never at the negotiating table.
Nava Vázquez said he was convinced that National Action will emerge strengthened from the internal elections on December 4 and 5, in which his successor will be elected.
"That (an alliance in 2012) is an issue that was never on the negotiating table, at least not for now, it was an approach for the local election that was successful and fulfilled the objective," he said.
The PAN leader said that the PAN is backed by 71 years of dialogue, so "we are not afraid of internal competition; On the contrary, "we enjoy it and it strengthens us," he said.
He said that without a doubt the council will know how to choose the best or the best leader that National Action requires for the next three years, hence it will deliver the coin "to whom the council determines."
"I have that absolute tranquility and openness, to any of the five I would be proud to hand over the office of the party president."
He predicted that the rebound that the party registered in the last elections on July 4 will be reflected in the next contests, although "it is not yet time to think about 2012."
"For now, it is about accompanying Governor Gabino Cué in this task."
In this context, he stressed that the three governments emanating from alliances in Oaxaca, Puebla and Sinaloa will be the flag and will be a reason for observation throughout the country, hence "many hopes, longings are placed in them, and I am sure that Gabino will live up to expectations."
When questioned about the PRI's criticism of President Felipe Calderon for his speech during the four years of his administration, Cesar Nava called on the PRI members to reflect on the six-year terms of former presidents Ernesto Zedillo and Carlos Salinas de Gortari.
"If the PRI thinks that the governments of Zedillo and Salinas were better than those of Fox and Calderon; that they begin to defend them; to come out," he said.
He said that the head of the federal executive can make expressions like those he made in his speech at the National Auditorium, because in the country there is no gag, much less censorship.
Obama Promotes Pro-Immigrant Law on Twitter
"If you agree that passing the Dream Act is appropriate, call your senators and urge them to pass this legislation," the US president tweeted on the popular social network.
President Barack Obama today joined the national mobilization in support of the Dream Act, to legalize undocumented students, with a message on his personal Twitter account.
"If you agree that passing the Dream Act is appropriate, call your senators and urge them to pass this legislation," Obama tweeted.
His brief message keeps open a cyber link to a broader document that asks the public to immediately communicate with senators, given that a vote on the legislation is imminent.
"With a vote expected to happen soon, now is the time to make your voice heard," he says.
The message came after all 42 Republican senators threatened to block voting on any legislation unless the extension of Bush-era tax cuts and government funding is passed.
Such a blockade, announced in a letter signed by the 42 Republican senators, could affect the vote of the Dream Act and other projects such as the ratification of the new START treaty with Russia against the proliferation of nuclear weapons.
Questioned about the Republican blockade of the Dream Act and other projects, presidential spokesman Robert Gibbs trusted that once the fiscal issue is resolved, a calendar can be set for the rest of the projects.
"I think there is a lot of time..."
"We all agree that we have to resolve the fiscal issue before the end of the year..."
"I think we can reach an agreement at some point in that and then we can plan the sequence of the rest," he said.
Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid announced Tuesday that he would call for a "close debate vote" on the Dream Act, so the bill to legalize undocumented students could be voted on as early as next Thursday in the Senate, although it is more likely next week.
The Senate version of the Dream Act would legalize about 800,000 young people who entered the United States before age 16, stayed in the country for the past five years and entered an institution of higher education or the military.
But supporters require 60 votes to approve the bill, requiring the help of a handful of Republicans, as pro-bill organizations lobby to ensure passage of the bill.
Democrats, most of whom support the Dream Act, hold 58 seats.
But at least one of them, Sen. Ben Nelson of Nebraska, has said he will vote against it, and only one Republican has expressed support for the bill, Richard Lugar of Indiana.
Therefore, supporters of the Dream Act need to add several Republicans in case other Democrats decide to turn their backs on the initiative.
Among the most courted Republicans are Maine Sens. Olympia Snowe and Susan Collins, as well as outgoing Sen. George Lemieux of Florida, who completed Sen. Mel Martinez's term.
Other Republicans who have supported the Dream Act in the past include Orrin Hatch of Utah and Kay Bailey Hutchinson of Texas but have said they will not endorse it another time.
Another Republican he supported, John McCain, has not defined his position at this time.
Although the House of Representatives has a different version, analysts agree that the Dream Act faces the biggest hurdles in the Senate.
With literature they put their finger on the wound
The second round of The Pleasures of Language was a walk where participants showed off the narration
"That of Sex on the tongue I understand but ... the finger on the sore? What is expected of me?", asked the writer Luisa Valenzuela invited to open the second round of Los placeres de la lengua, a cycle that celebrates literature in Spanish and that this time used the subtitle of her question (in another fair the round table was dedicated to Sex in the language, she explained).
The finger on the wound... "It puts us in trouble," the Argentine writer snapped sweetly to the audience, mostly young people, who gathered at the Guadalajara International Book Fair (FIL) to listen to this round table moderated by Marisol Shultz and where Valenzuela, Sergio Ramírez, Mayra Montero and Luis García Montero participated.
Luisa Valenzuela read a text that she dedicated to Gonzalo Celorio and that Shultz would later define as a great story, with Luisa in the first person as the protagonist who, in search of knowing what the "sore" is, goes from doctor to doctor, from which she does not get answers although she does get clues in the same narrative thread.
From the infectologist she leaves convinced: "patience is not my forte, maybe it is my sore".
In the end, after a frustrated approach with the traumatologist who has stolen his breath in the middle of the corridor, but who clarifies that sore is not a scientific term; It is the psychoanalyst who reveals the mystery: "The wound is the real open, the symbolic is the scar."
The protagonist breathed a sigh of relief and concluded "from the wound I only managed to know that it is the real open and that it does not exist", but convinced that the pleasures and traps of the language must be very intertwined.
Valenzuela, the writer, played with both.
The Nicaraguan Sergio Ramírez also presented a delightful narrative that he titled Elogio de la invención, where the finger on the wound is not named but in a moment it is discovered.
With touches of magical realism, it tells of a famous sorceress, who also touched clouds, brought back men who had gone far or repaired the virtues that a maiden had lost, a narrative that turned to speak later America, the great novel that did not lack from the beginning its own chroniclers who told it and quoted Bernal Díaz del Castillo who criticizes the excesses of what was told by the Conquering captains.
"Cervantes who invented us all (the writers) made fun of the feigned witnesses who appeared in the stories presented as real, but otherwise the story of America would never have been told with imagination that lacked to the point of modesty."
However, he stressed "it is the crazy and the deceiver who best imagine" and it is where reality and lies converge, where it is no longer known that what is narrated belongs to one side or another, where fiction literature reaches its apogee.
He actually calls it the 'Cervantes tradition'.
"By his inheritance we are what is counted."
In her turn, the writer Mayra Montero noted and applauded the variety of interpretations that gave rise to the invitation of the FIL with her round table The finger in the wound.
The Cuban-Puerto Rican pointed hers towards the great wound of social violence that crosses her country – and shares Latin America – as a result of disputes over drug trafficking and sales.
"I believe that good literature, good poetry, good songs contain a tacit commitment that of course is not premeditated," he said, after citing that the reality of literature is communication and the dimension of the commitment established between author and readers, and that in a "chemical reaction" of the latter.
The night was closed by the Spanish poet Luis García Montero, whose speech also emphasized "that finger on the wound of the writer's committed writer."
He considered that in a world that lives in a hurry, also in intellectual customs and control of consciences that results in dogmatism, forgetting "that behind each affirmation there is a small no and behind each denial there is a small yes".
"To be masters of our thinking and to be masters of reality we have to nuance: and nuance often means putting our finger on the wound and annoying those people who are much more comfortable thinking in caricature, in black and white, in established ideas and without nuance and also annoy the powers that prefer a world in black and white, "  he said, inviting us to regain the sense of writing.
Romano goes for his first title
Rubén Omar Romano has three defeats in finals, has had ups and downs in his career, but has already managed to reach the decisive series three times.
With the duel of Santos Laguna and Monterrey in the final, they also face two different styles marked by their technicians, who find each other with a contrast marked by the results.
Rubén Omar Romano has three defeats in finals, he has had ups and downs in his career, but he has already managed to reach the decisive series three times, although so far he has gone blank and that is why this occasion is very special for him.
The Argentine has ended up comforting himself with the medal of the runner-up, he has been one step behind the winners and curiously with the same team he has played consecutive finals.
The Santista strategist reached his first final as a coach in the Apertura 2002 Tournament, when he was in charge of Morelia with which he fell 4-2 on aggregate against Toluca; later, in the Clausura 2003 also reached the decisive duel and also lost it with aggregate of 3-1 and was precisely against Rayados.
Already with Santos Laguna, in the 2010 Bicentennial Tournament, again against the Devils, Rubén again suffered a setback, as his team ended up tied 2-2 against the choriceros after 210 minutes of play, but in the penaltis shootout he took a 3-1 lead with two opportunities to seal the title for finally three of his players failed from the 11 steps and suffered the 4-3 somersault.
Rubén has already lost two finals with the Red Devils and one with Monterrey, his rival in turn, therefore he does not want to suffer the same fate, he seeks to get rid of the curse and be able to celebrate a title for the first time, although he affirms that for him the most important thing is the institution.
"I want to be champion, I do not want to break any statistics, this is for a club, for a hobby to which I owe myself and consequently the title will come for me, but the above is the most important thing," said the helmsman when questioned about the numbers he has against playing finals.
Very valid has the previous final, from which, he says, he has learned a lot, "the only lesson we can have is that until the referee whistles the end we can not celebrate, we are prepared in the line, the players too, because the previous time, with two penalties to shoot we were already prepared to run away and I think that is a lesson,  Until the game is over, we can celebrate."
Knowing that this series could be defined in penalty kicks, something that does not worry him, because he trusts his players: "One never seeks to reach the penalty shootout, one seeks to finish in regular time, but sometimes there is no other and you have to be prepared, in the previous tournament we were prepared, unfortunately fate made us a bad move,  Sometimes because of nerves or the anxiety of having the title in our hands, but it went away, that left us something for this final that we hope does not reach that instance. "
Romano has in his hands to stop being a runner-up technician and taste for the first time the glory that titles give.
EU changes rules to obtain visa
Individuals should go to the Visa Applicant Service Centers prior to their interview at the Consular Section; The cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
As of January 10, 2011, the procedure for processing a visa at the U.S. Embassy and consulates will change.
Under the new procedure, most applicants will need to go to Visa Applicant Service (ASC) centers prior to their interview at the Consular Section.
ASC staff will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section prior to the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, among which are:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to make the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and another one for the courier to deliver the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment that will cover all three services.
The current fee will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for petition-based visas (including temporary worker visas) and $390 for merchant and investor visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to attend an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be collected at the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed at the Consular Section will stay in the Consular Section less time than in the past.
Likewise, those who apply for visas at the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of $ 26.
For additional information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
NASA to announce finding of extraterrestrial life
The US space agency summoned the press to present tomorrow a finding that will cause impact in the search for living beings in space.
The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) of the United States will announce tomorrow, Thursday, an astrobiological discovery, which could prove the theory that extraterrestrial life does exist.
The finding will be presented at a press conference tomorrow Thursday at 1:00 p.m. at NASA headquarters in Washington by experts in astrobiology, science described as the one in charge of studying the origin, evolution, distribution and future of life in the Universe.
Citing the press, NASA said it will present "a finding that will cause impact in the search for extraterrestrial life," which raised speculation from experts in other countries.
The discovery could prove the theory that there are creatures alongside us and in hostile environments that were thought uninhabitable, and would put on the table the possibility of them becoming intelligent beings like humans if the conditions in which they live improve.
It is apparently a microbe that was found at the bottom of Mono Lake in Yosemite National Park, California, where it lives in an environment that was thought too poisonous for any form of life, since the lake is rich in arsenic.
Somehow, the creature uses arsenic as a way to survive and this ability increases the possibility that similar life could exist on other planets, which do not have our benevolent atmosphere.
According to astrobiologists, if these organisms use arsenic in their metabolism, it will be shown that "there is another form of life, a second form of life, different from the one we know."
The space agency will announce the true scope of the findings at a press conference on Thursday.
The conference will be attended by geobiologist Pamela Conrad, who studies the possibility of life on Mars; and biologist Steven Benner, one of the scientists studying Titan (Saturn's largest moon), under the perspective that its chemistry is similar to that of Earth.
Gesta PRD, PT, Convergencia and Patrón 'bloc' opponent
With reforms to the Organic Law of Congress, it gives rise to the arrival of 'bipartisanship', they denounce.
The 60th Legislature was not installed when an opposition bloc emerged in Congress, headed by the deputies of the PRD, PT, Convergence and Jesús Manuel Patrón Montalvo, who declared himself independent, and the four questioned one thing: the arrival of 'bipartisanship' to the Chamber.
Before starting the installation session of the 60th Legislature, Felipe Manzanarez Rodríguez, of Convergencia; Ezequiel Reynoso Esparza, of the PT; Javier Corvera Quevedo, of the PRD; and Patrón Montalvo, 'thundered' against the reform of the Organic Law, since it excluded them.
With this reform, they reiterated, the 'bipartisanship' begins, because now it will be two people, from an equal number of parties, who will control Congress.
These four deputies, along with Gloria Margarita Santos Aguilar, coordinator of the PRD, were the only ones who voted against the Board of Directors, headed by PAN member Salvador López Brito and Luis Antonio Cárdenas Fonseca, in his capacity as vice president.
Corvera Quevedo explained that with these reforms in an institutional way, political marginality on the part of the PRI and PAN is constituted.
He explained that in the coming days they will talk with the representatives of the PAN and PRI to modify the scheme, based on a political will, and if they do not have it, then they will be overwhelmed again by both parties and with it the opposition coalition is over.
"This is how far (the opposition coalition) has come, that's what I look at, because we are excluded, from any decision, they don't even have the political deference to consider the opinion of the rest."
Felipe Manzanarez Rodríguez, of Convergencia, mentioned that with the PRD, PT and Patrón, there are coincidences and that is why they are forming a plural group.
It cannot be allowed, he continued, that Congress, after having been monopolistic, now be "duopoly."
"It is not the spirit of law reform that there is eternal bipartisanship in Congress."
To begin with, this group is starting with 5 legislators, and they are talking with other comrades to make them more, the convergent added.
Ezequiel Reynoso Esparza, of the PT, explained that Congress has now become a "booty" between two, alluding to the PAN and PRI.
"Before it was just one game, now they are dividing it between two."
Patron Montalvo, asked that the personality of the deputy be respected, that he be given his place at the negotiating tables.
"That not by cupular agreements, it is left out to 5 that we are probably going to make 9 deputies, right now to the five who see us, separated into different fractions, we have decided to unify to seek a place at the negotiating table, that is the issue that in the reform that they made that they agreed, we are out and we do not agree with that reform. "
$200,000 more for "the provider"
Mazatlan City Council pays another check to the questioned owner of electrical material company.
One more check for just over 200 thousand pesos in favor of Lorena Guadalupe Camacho Palazuelos was issued by the City Council.
With this, the amount that has been paid in this second semester to the owner of the electrical material company, amounts to 1 million 200 thousand pesos.
According to the transparency page of the Municipality, this last check number 9258447 was issued on November 16, for the amount of 200 thousand 144.56 pesos, under the concept of "settlement of accounts payable".
Treasurer Luis Miguel López Moreno had announced that more money would come out of the Commune in favor of this supplier, which was observed by the Superior State Audit for selling at a higher price.
What has not been reported is the total still owed to him and, therefore, how many more checks remain to be issued in favor of Camacho Palazuelos.
"Nothing has been bought, you're just being paid what you owe, just like the rest of the suppliers," he said in an interview.
The last checks "reappeared" in the last quarter of the year: September 24, two of October 15, October 19, October 29 and the latter, of November 16.
Although the provider has not yet been published in the Official State Gazette, as the Law marks when a company is questioned by the ASE, in order to prevent other governments from using its services, the Treasurer assured that they have not used their services again.
The above, after July 25, Noroeste published a review of the checks issued by the City Council to its suppliers, in which it was revealed that, from March 2008 to July 9, 2010, in the triennium of Mayor Jorge Abel López Sánchez, Camacho Palazuelos was paid by the Municipality more than 10 million pesos,  through 42 checks.
He also made transactions with Jumapam, where he cashed checks for more than 3 million pesos.
They urge to attend tourist sites
Lament tourism entrepreneurs accident of foreign tourist by poor conditions of the Glorieta Sánchez Taboada in Mazatlan.
After the fall of a foreign tourist in a sinking of the Glorieta Sánchez Taboada, the tourism sector of Mazatlan asked the authorities to give attention to the areas and sites that are in poor condition and that project a bad image of the port.
Salvador Barraza Rubio, president of the Association of Merchants of the Golden Zone, recalled that on different occasions they have denounced that the image of the destination is taken care of and reverse the bad that tourists find with new activities or routes.
He said the poor state of the streets and sidewalks has affected because tourists come for a walk and see the disorder and turn around nearby businesses.
"Politicians do not know what it is to close a company one day and have no idea of the money that is lost, or else they would not do the works in this way in so long and without proper planning."
Hotelier José Ramón Manguart Sánchez said that the fall of the tourist exposed the lack of prevention and maintenance by the City Council.
"The municipality will have to assume its responsibility and prevent it from happening again, how to do it because giving preventive maintenance and not falling only into the corrective," he said.
"We are eager to enjoy a clean city, because not only because it is a tourist area must be maintained, but as inhabitants we deserve a clean place to live and the City Council must change its strategy to keep the city well."
There are other sites that also look neglected and incomplete, he said, such as the Shield and the Venadito de Mazatlán.
"Nowadays, for tourists to come, it does not depend solely on promotion, there has to be a good product, a city that has cleanliness on its beaches, on its avenues, permanent maintenance in what are the tourist attractions," he said.
"Due attention has not been given and this type of event highlights something that is notorious by all, maintenance is needed."
Raúl Llera Martínez, Undersecretary of Tourism Promotion, said that the rescue of tourist sites in Mazatlan is urgent, because they are not used correctly and project a bad image.
He spoke of a series of places that must be put in line together with the municipality and be a priority to have the city up to date, clean, orderly and attractive because it is of tourist vocation.
"Fortunately, Mazatlan offers many sites and historical and cultural places that will have to be ordered first, cleaned and put in line to make them attractive to be able to add them in the inventory we have to promote the destination."
Ask Congress for results
Eduardo Dávalos, president of the CCE, proposed that the deputies assume the great responsibility of being an example of seeing for a better Sinaloa for the various challenges it faces.
A Legislature of decent work and free of agreements between parties and the State Executive claims the business sector of Mazatlan, because there is a convulsed Sinaloa that faces great problems.
Since yesterday, the 60th legislature was installed, composed of seven political forces, 19 deputies from the PRI, 13 from the PAN, three from the New Alliance Party, two from the PRD, one from the PT, one from Convergence and one more from the PVEM, which adds up to a total of 40 popular representatives.
