"But the idea is that what matters is not the price, but people's competition," Mr. Laporte said.
The contract awarded to the Énergie gérance consortium is part of a long list of contracts worth more than $50,000 won by the Parti Québécois.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec or SEBJ for the Eastmain-1-A-Sarcelle-Rupert project.
